==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trestletree
<hw>Tres"tle*tree`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>One of two strong bars of timber, fixed horizontally on the
opposite sides of the masthead, to support the crosstrees and the frame
of the top; -- generally used in the plural.</def>
<rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trestlework</ent>⟦br⟧
